# PM Mode Rules

## Development Flow

Development is carried out in the following phases.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    %% AI Modes
    subgraph Modes [AI Modes]
        direction LR
        PMMode[PM Mode<br>Project Management]
        PMOMode[PMO Mode<br>Rule Compliance Check]
        ArchMode[Architect Mode<br>System Design]
        CodeMode[Code Mode<br>Implementation & Test]
    end

    %% Main Flow
    Start([Start]) --> RC[1.Rule<br>Check]
    RC --> RD[2.Requirements<br>Definition]
    RD --> DS[3.Design]
    DS --> IM[4.Implementation]
    IM --> TS[5.Testing]

    %% Common processing at the end of phase (Placed below main flow)
    subgraph PhaseEnd [Processing at End of Phase]
        direction LR
        Commit[git commit<br>deliverables]
        --> Review[Request Review<br>from User]
    end

    %% Connection between each phase and end processing (Towards bottom right)
    RC --> PhaseEnd
    RD --> PhaseEnd
    DS --> PhaseEnd
    IM --> PhaseEnd
    TS --> PhaseEnd

    PhaseEnd --> NextPhase{Is there<br>a next phase?}
    NextPhase -->|Yes| NextStart[To Next Phase]
    NextPhase -->|No| End([Complete])

    %% Relation between modes and each phase (Arrows from top to bottom)
    PMMode -.-> RD
    PMOMode -.-> RC
    PMOMode -.-> PMOCheck
    ArchMode -.-> DS
    CodeMode -.-> IM
    CodeMode -.-> TS

    %% Style Definition
    classDef phaseNode fill:#f5f5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px
    class RC,RD,DS,IM,TS phaseNode

    classDef processNode fill:#fff5f5,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px
    class PMOCheck,Commit,Review,Correct processNode

    classDef modeNode fill:#e6f7ff,stroke:#0066cc,stroke-width:1px
    class PMMode,PMOMode,ArchMode,CodeMode modeNode

    classDef decisionNode fill:#fffbf5,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px
    class Fix,NextPhase decisionNode
```

## Requirements Definition Phase

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Start Req Def]) --> RD1[Create Branch]
    RD1 --> RD1a[feature/feature-name]
    RD1 --> RD1b[fix/bug-name]
    RD1 --> RD1c[hotfix/urgent-bug-name]
    RD1a --> RD2[Create Requirements/Feature List]
    RD1b --> RD2
    RD1c --> RD2
    RD2 --> RD3[Document in<br>docs/requirements-definition.md]
    RD3 --> RD4[Follow markdownlint<br>standard rules]
    RD4 --> End([Req Def Complete])

    classDef reqNode fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px
    class RD1,RD1a,RD1b,RD1c,RD2,RD3,RD4 reqNode
```

1. Branch Name: Create a git branch with `feature/[feature-name]`, `fix/[bug-name]`, or `hotfix/[urgent-bug-name]` and start work.
2. List the requirements and features for the given instructions in `docs/requirements-definition.md`.

- Create md files according to standard markdownlint rules.

### Document Creation Conventions

#### requirements-definition.md

1. Requirements Definition Document Structure

   - Project Overview
   - Functional Requirements List
   - Non-functional Requirements List
   - Constraints
   - Prerequisites

2. Feature List Format
   - Feature ID
   - Feature Name
   - Feature Overview
   - Priority
   - Dependencies
   - Constraints

#### markdownlint Conventions

- Indent with 2 spaces
- Use heading levels in order
- Specify language for code blocks
- Use consistent symbols for lists
- Max 2 newlines (between blocks)
